      What is the message of Rosemary's Baby?
      In Rosemary's Baby, no matter how hard Rosemary attempts to regain her identity, she is pushed to conform to others' expectations. Therefore, the film asserts, no matter how hard women attempt to escape these constructs, they are continuously manipulated, lied to, and dragged back into them.14 gen 2020

      Is there a remake of Rosemary's Baby?
      Rosemary's Baby is a 2014 two-part, four-hour television miniseries adaptation of Ira Levin's best-selling 1967 horror novel of the same name and its 1997 sequel Son of Rosemary. Zoe Saldana stars in the NBC production, directed by Agnieszka Holland. Unlike earlier versions, it is set in Paris rather than New York.

      What is the story rosemary baby about?
      A young wife comes to believe that her offspring is not of this world. Waifish Rosemary Woodhouse (Mia Farrow) and her struggling actor husband Guy (John Cassavetes) move to a New York City apartment building with an ominous reputation and odd neighbors Roman and Minnie Castavet (Sidney Blackmer, Ruth Gordon). When Rosemary becomes pregnant she becomes increasingly isolated, and the diabolical truth is revealed only after Rosemary gives birth.

      Descrizione

      Rivisitazione in chiave moderna del romanzo di Ira Levin: dopo essersi trasferita a Parigi, Rosemary rimane incinta, ma il futuro nascituro stato preso di mira da una presenza diabolica.
      Data di uscita: 24 dicembre 1968 (Italia)
      Regista: Roman Polaski
      Botteghino: 33,4 milioni USD
      Premi: Oscar alla miglior attrice non protagonista, ALTRO
      Adattato da: Rosemary's Baby
      Distribuito da: Paramount Pictures
